content:
Some shell command when using Anaconda
Table of Contents Installation Usage Check installed package Check virtual environment Update conda Create env Remove env Activate/Deactivate env Install package Remove package Clone env Clean conda Remove package Usage of environment.yaml Usage of requirements.txt Installation Please search it on official website Usage Check installed package conda list
Check virtual environment conda env list or conda info -e
Update conda conda update conda
Create env conda create -n &lt;env_name&gt; python=3.x
Remove env conda remove -n &lt;env_name&gt; --all
Activate/Deactivate env For Linux/MacOS source activate &lt;env_name&gt;
source deactivate &lt;env_name&gt;
For Windows/Linux/MacOS conda activate &lt;env_name&gt;
conda deactivate &lt;env_name&gt;
Install package conda install &lt;package_name&gt;=&lt;version&gt;
e.g. conda install numpy=1.22.0
Remove package conda uninstall &lt;package_name&gt;
Clone env conda create -n &lt;new_env&gt; --clone &lt;old_env&gt;
Clean conda conda clean --all
Remove package conda remove -n &lt;env_name&gt; &lt;package_name&gt;
Usage of environment.yaml Export env into yaml file conda env export &gt; environment.yaml
Create new env from yaml file conda env create -f environment.yaml
Usage of requirements.txt conda install --yes --file requirements.txt

Some pip commands.
Usage Install package pip install &lt;package_name&gt;
pip install &lt;package_name&gt;==&lt;version&gt;
requirements.txt Create a requirements.txt pip freeze &gt;requirements.txt
Install packages from requirements.txt pip install -r requirements.txt
